Related: bount, enough, plent, pover, sufficient


Abundance would be goal if it weren't for the profit,
Of usury through scarcity when hoarding work sources.

 This dependence is enforced by vassals with needs.
 Externalizing costs until good is bad, & bad good.

 Usury hates freedom, for it is bad for the market.
 What if tools were free and control was autarchic?

 Brave owners limit hoarding by leasing for 'free'.
 Making available "at cost" to renters who qualify.

   The GPL is the GNU plan to internalize cost,
   Making abundance again good by taxing power.
